{"title_page": "Mestre Ferradura", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mestre Ferradura\n| image              = [[File:MestreFerradura 2.jpg|200px|Mestre Ferradura 2]]\n| native_name        = Omri Ferradura Breda\n| birth_date         = January 22, 1976\n| alma_mater         = [[Universidade Federal do Estado do Rio de Janeiro]]\n| occupation         = President of the Brazilian Capoeira-Education Institute\nDirector of the Brincadeira de Angola Project\n}} \n[[File:MestreFerradura.jpg|alt=Mestre Ferradura|thumb|Mestre Ferradura in an early children education school.]]\n'''Omri Ferradura Breda''', commonly known as '''Mestre Ferradura''' (January 22, 1976), is a ''[[Capoeira|Mestre de Capoeira]]'', [[Pedagogy|pedagogue]], [[president (corporate title)|president]] of the Brazilian Institute of Capoeira Education, and [[director (business)|director]] of the [[Capoeira angola|Brincadeira de Angola]] project.\n\n== Biography ==\nMaster Ferradura started practicing [[Capoeira]] in 1991, at [[Rio de Janeiro]], at Mestre Marrom's [[Capoeira angola|Capoeira Angola]]. He started teaching Capoeira in 1993. Mestre Ferradura received his graduation by the Capoeira Master Henrique Anastacio de Jesus, the Mestre Marrom, in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Portal da Capoeira|url=http://www.capoeira.gov.br/user/infor/2200|work=www.capoeira.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-27}}</ref> He graduated in [[pedagogy]] from the [[Federal University of the State of Rio de Janeiro]], and specialized in [[Early childhood education|Early Childhood Education]]. He is the founder and coordenator of Brincadeira de Angola Project, which has the purpose of the playful teaching of capoeira applied to early childhood education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cepe.usp.br/wp-content/uploads/Mestre-Ferradura.pdf|title=CEPE USP|date=|accessdate=|publisher=|last=|first=}}</ref> The Brazilian Institute of Capoeira Education, project which he's president, he helps teachers to understand the concepts of Capoeira Education.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura|url=https://capoeiraibce.com/mestre-ferradura/|work=IBCE|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== Contributions to the Capoeira Education field ===\nMaster Ferradura possesses broad projection while difunding the Brincadeira de Angola method, which is a pedagic-philosophic based on the educational potential, applying Capoeira as a [[Pedagogy of the Oppressed|transformative pedagogic]] practice in autonomous subjects formation, and deconstruction of racism through the valorization of the african roots.<ref>{{cite web|title=Capoeira na escola \u00e9 uma janela para a desconstru\u00e7\u00e3o do racismo|url=https://ceert.org.br/noticias/educacao/25233/capoeira-na-escola-e-uma-janela-para-a-desconstrucao-do-racismo|work=CEERT|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura&#8217;s Great Insight on the Importance of Capoeira&#8217;s African Roots|url=https://www.capoeiranewsonline.com/mestre-ferraduras-great-insight-on-the-importance-of-capoeiras-african-roots/|work=www.capoeiranewsonline.com|date=2016-09-07|accessdate=2020-02-28|first=Rolha|last=Capoeira}}</ref> The basis of the methology is the ancestral knowledge of Capoeira, passed on from master to disciple in a traditional way. By balancing these popular and academic knowledge, the Brincadeira de Angola method suggest a Capoeira Pedagogy.<ref>{{cite web|title=17 de julho de 2019 - I\u00ea Camar\u00e1|url=https://tribunadoceara.com.br/blogs/ie-camara/2019/07/17/|work=tribunadoceara.com.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref> Another contribution by Mestre Ferradura to the Capoeira community was the production of \"''Movimento Novo''\" (New Movement), along with Mestre Itapu\u00e3 Beira-Mar, which brought discussions around the resulting violence  from the contact of capoeirists from different schools and proposes a pacific interaction to the new generations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Capoeira: O \u00daltimo Movimento Novo (Com V\u00eddeos)|url=https://capoeirariodejaneiro.com.br/geral/movimento-novo/|work=Capoeira - Rio|date=2019-01-03|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Capoeira |first1=Nestor |title=Capoeira: pequeno manual do jogador |date=1998 |publisher=Editora Record |isbn=978-85-01-04879-0 |url= |language=pt}}</ref>\n\n== Research and academic production ==\nIn the past decade, Mestre Ferradura has acted in the formation of teacher and promoting his pedagogic methodology in Brazil and Europe. His influences include [[Paulo Freire]], Muniz Sodr\u00e9, [[Marshall Rosenberg|Marshall Rosemberg]], Emilia Viotti da Costa, Elisa Larkin Nascimento, [[Thomas Skidmore|Thomas E. Skidmore]], Nestor Capoeira, [[Michel Foucault|Michel Foucalt]], [[A. S. Neill|A.S. Neil]], Terry Orlick, and [[Peter Slade]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - Biblioteca - Educa\u00e7\u00e3o F\u00edsica e jogos|url=http://www.educacaopublica.rj.gov.br/biblioteca/educacao_fisica/0009.html|work=www.educacaopublica.rj.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref> In his academic outreach, Mestre Ferradura travels and joins a number of formation programs and training of teachers and ''mestres'' in Brazilian and international Universities. Among the institutions which his courses and symposia have been ministrated, are included [[Federal Rural University of Rio de Janeiro|UFRR]], [[Federal University of Bahia|UFBA]], [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]], and ''Museu da Rep\u00fablica''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/rr/noticia/2013/11/mestres-dunga-e-ferradura-fazem-oficinas-de-capoeira-na-ufrr.html|title=Mestres Dunga e Ferradura fazem oficinas de capoeira na UFRR|date=|accessdate=|publisher=Globoesporte.com|last=|first=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=O ensino e a difus\u00e3o da capoeira foi debatido no XV Enecult \u2013 ENECULT|url=http://www.cult.ufba.br/enecult/o-ensino-e-a-difusao-da-capoeira-foi-debatido-no-xv-enecult/|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=CEPEUSP - Centro de Pr\u00e1ticas Esportivas da USP \u2013 Simp\u00f3sio Internacional de Capoeira|url=http://www.cepe.usp.br/?news=simposio-internacional-de-capoeira|work=www.cepe.usp.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura|url=http://museus.cultura.gov.br/evento/5370/|work=Mapas Culturais|date=2019-05-08|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-BR|first=Mapas|last=Culturais}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Projeto Capoeirando ter\u00e1 aulas gratuitas para o p\u00fablico infantil|url=https://www.correiodoestado.com.br/arte-e-cultura/projeto-capoeirando-encerra-ciclo-de-formacao-para-professores-com/356973/|work=Correio do Estado|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Goi\u00e2nia recebe curso de Forma\u00e7\u00e3o Continuada em Capoeira na Educa\u00e7\u00e3o Infantil {{!}} Revista Zelo|url=http://revistazelo.com.br/post/goiania-recebe-curso-de-formacao-continuada-em-capoeira-na-educacao-infantil|work=revistazelo.com.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nHis most notable articles are:\n\n* ''Capoeira as a transformative educational practive''  (2010)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* ''Capoeira as pedagogic practice in early childhood education''  (2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=Revista Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - A Capoeira como pr\u00e1tica pedag\u00f3gica na Educa\u00e7\u00e3o Infantil|url=https://educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br/artigos/15/12/a-capoeira-como-prtica-pedaggica-na-educao-infantil|work=educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* ''Capoeira as a libertarian education for the formation of autonomous subjects - the teaching practices in Rio de Janeiro's Rodas de Rua'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|title=Revista Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - Capoeira e educa\u00e7\u00e3o libert\u00e1ria para forma\u00e7\u00e3o de sujeitos aut\u00f4nomos \u2013 as pr\u00e1ticas de ensino nas rodas de rua do Rio de Janeiro|url=https://educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br/artigos/19/28/capoeira-e-educacao-libertaria-para-formacao-de-sujeitos-autonomos-r-as-praticas-de-ensino-nas-rodas-de-rua-do-rio-de-janeiro|work=educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* ''Brazilian racial ideology: the subjacent racism in comics magazines'' (2015)<ref>{{cite journal|last=Campos|first=Abigail Ferreira|date=2019-10-17|title=O CONCEITO DE IDEOLOGIA NAS HIST\u00d3RIAS EM QUADRINHOS|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.22533/at.ed.18519171026|publisher=Atena Editora|pages=283\u2013290|isbn=978-85-7247-718-5}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Capoeira de Rua.jpg|alt=Mestre Ferradura|thumb|Mestre Ferradura conducting a circle of Capoeira de Rua.|left]]\nHis works are academic references in authors of varied fields of pedagogy and studies in the african matrix, influencing and being cited in a series of monographies in Brasil.<ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Concep\u00e7\u00f5es de origem do ser humano e os conhecimentos das religi\u00f5es de matriz africana|url=http://repositorio.im.ufrrj.br:8080/jspui/bitstream/1235813/2932/1/Bruno%20Batista%20Cassiano%20-%20Jun%202016.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio UFRRJ|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=A capoeira como ferramenta metodol\u00f3gica na educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil: um relato de pr\u00e1ticas educativas|url=https://monografias.ufrn.br/jspui/bitstream/123456789/7147/10/CapoeiraFerramentaMetodo_Monografia_2018.pdf|journal=Monografias UFRN|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Uma interven\u00e7\u00e3o psicopedag\u00f3gica para educadores sociais de capoeira|url=https://www.editorarealize.com.br/revistas/conedu/trabalhos/TRABALHO_EV073_MD1_SA1_ID1065_21082017143144.pdf|journal=IV Congresso Nacional de Educa\u00e7\u00e3o - CONEDU|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=CONTRIBUI\u00c7\u00c3O DA CAPOEIRA NO PROGRAMA MAIS EDUCA\u00c7\u00c3O PARA A PROMO\u00c7\u00c3O DA CULTURA AFRO-BRASILEIRA: a experi\u00eancia de um Centro Integrado de Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica em Santa B\u00e1rbara d\u2019Oeste/SP|url=https://unisal.br/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Disserta%C3%A7%C3%A3o_Elisangela-L.-F.-de-Moraes.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio de Monografias da UNISAL|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=O conv\u00edvio da diferen\u00e7a: pr\u00e1ticas biopol\u00edticas no jogo de dentro e no jogo de fora|url=https://tede2.pucsp.br/bitstream/handle/21858/2/Livia%20Sernache%20Rios.pdf|journal=Resposit\u00f3rio de Disserta\u00e7\u00f5es PUC-SP|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=CAPOEIRA ANGOLA NA ESCOLA MUNICIPAL NOVA MORADA: perspectivas e pr\u00e1ticas educativas na constru\u00e7\u00e3o das identidades culturais|url=http://ww2.ppgeci.ufrpe.br/sites/ww2.ppgeci.ufrpe.br/files/documentos/dissertacao_ppgeci_n._30_danilo_santos_do_vale.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio do Programa de P\u00f3s-Gradua\u00e7\u00e3o da UFPE|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n== Social action ==\n\n\nMestre Ferradura's participations in social action includes occasional participation in activities of the Third Sector to regular governamental projects, such as:{{Quote box|quote=When we bring Capoeira de Rua for them, is a bit of culture and visibility. At the same time, we bring the idea of social circle, the look eye-in-the-eye, the care, the shelter, the belonging, and the knowledge that in that circle, you are just one capoeirist.|source=\u2014Mestre Ferradura, in an interview to Brazilian news program \"Balan\u00e7o Geral\", in December, 2019. [27]|align=right|width=33%}}{{Quote box|quote=Homeless people goes through a process of invisibilization. At Capeoira, we have necessarily to look at each other, interact, touch, know a bit of our feelings and needs of each other. The student's self-esteem is enhanced when he's seen, when he's heard, in his most basic needs of care, shelter, and belonging.|source=\u2014Mestre Ferradura, in interview to [[Rede Globo]], in August, 2019. [28]|align=right|width=33%}}\n\n* At the Benjamin Constant Institute, with a project of educating Capoeira to blind children<ref>{{cite web|title=Alunos fazem exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de capoeira aos pais|url=http://www.ibc.gov.br/component/content/article?id=865|work=www.ibc.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n* At [[:pt:Departamento_Geral_de_A\u00e7\u00f5es_S\u00f3cio_Educativas|DEGASE]], with institutionalized teenagers serving socio-educational measures<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bueno|first=Luzia|date=2005-12-15|title=G\u00eaneros da M\u00eddia Impressa no Material Did\u00e1tico e a Not\u00edcia Adaptada|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.5433/2237-4876.2005v8n2p9|journal=Signum: Estudos da Linguagem|volume=8|number=2|pages=9|doi=10.5433/2237-4876.2005v8n2p9|issn=2237-4876|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Carioca nota 10: Mestre Ferradura|url=https://vejario.abril.com.br/cidade/capoeirista-aulas-populacao-situacao-rua/|language=pt-BR}}</ref>\n* The Capoeira de Rua, with homeless people<ref>{{cite journal|date=2019-12-11|title=Vidas Invis\u00edveis: s\u00e9rie mostra um novo perfil dos moradores de rua|url=https://noticias.r7.com/rio-de-janeiro/balanco-geral-rj/videos/vidas-invisiveis-serie-mostra-um-novo-perfil-dos-moradores-de-rua-11122019|journal=R7.com|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Como Ser\u00e1? {{!}} Rede de solidariedade ajuda pessoas em situa\u00e7\u00e3o de rua no Rio de Janeiro {{!}} Globoplay|url=https://globoplay.globo.com/v/7863697/|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* The Brazilian Capoeira-Education Institute for the Peace, in partnership with Gingando Pela Paz, [[UNESCO]], and [[:pt:Viva_Rio|Viva Rio]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Gingando pela Paz Haiti completa quatro anos|url=http://vivario.org.br/gingando-pela-paz-haiti-completa-quatro-anos/|work=Viva Rio|date=2012-10-01|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n\n== Artistic contributions ==\nIn the artistic fields, Mestre Ferradura has worked in a variety of direction of Capoeira, like:\n\n* ''Intr\u00e9pida Trupe'', in the Kronos show, having participated in the front commission of [[Mocidade Independente de Padre Miguel]], which won the ''Tamborim de Ouro'' Award in 1999.\n* With Paola Barreto Leblanc, when signed the direction of Capoeira and writing the script of the \"Mar\u00e9 Capoeira\" movie.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mar\u00e9 Capoeira|url=http://portacurtas.org.br/filme/?name=mare_capoeira|work=Porta Curtas|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br|last=PortaCurtas}}</ref>\n* With Jo\u00e3o Falc\u00e3o, director of \"[[\u00d3pera do Malandro]]\", when he did body conditioning of the troup at [[Theatro Municipal (Rio de Janeiro)|Theatro Municipal do Rio de Janeiro]].\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [http://www.capoeira.gov.br/user/infor/2200 Portal da Capoeira]\n* [https://capoeiraibce.com/ Instituto Brasileiro de Capoeira-Educa\u00e7\u00e3o]\n* [http://www.brincadeiradeangola.com.br/ Projeto Brincadeira de Angola]\n* [https://capoeirariodejaneiro.com.br/ Capoeira Rio de Janeiro]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Capoeira mestres]]\n[[Category:Brazilian capoeira practitioners]]\n[[Category:Pedagogy]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mestre Ferradura\n| image              = [[File:MestreFerradura 2.jpg|200px|Mestre Ferradura 2]]\n| native_name        = Omri Ferradura Breda\n| birth_date         = January 22, 1976\n| alma_mater         = [[Universidade Federal do Estado do Rio de Janeiro]]\n| occupation         = President of the Brazilian Capoeira-Education Institute\nDirector of the Brincadeira de Angola Project\n}} \n[[File:MestreFerradura.jpg|alt=Mestre Ferradura|thumb|Mestre Ferradura in an early children education school.]]\n'''Omri Ferradura Breda''', commonly known as '''Mestre Ferradura''' (January 22, 1976), is a ''[[Capoeira|Mestre de Capoeira]]'', [[Pedagogy|pedagogue]], [[president (corporate title)|president]] of the Brazilian Institute of Capoeira Education, and [[director (business)|director]] of the [[Capoeira angola|Brincadeira de Angola]] project.\n\n== Biography ==\nMaster Ferradura started practicing [[Capoeira]] in 1991, at [[Rio de Janeiro]], at Mestre Marrom's [[Capoeira angola|Capoeira Angola]]. He started teaching Capoeira in 1993. Mestre Ferradura received his graduation by the Capoeira Master Henrique Anastacio de Jesus, the Mestre Marrom, in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Portal da Capoeira|url=http://www.capoeira.gov.br/user/infor/2200|work=www.capoeira.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-27}}</ref> He graduated in [[pedagogy]] from the [[Federal University of the State of Rio de Janeiro]], and specialized in [[Early childhood education|Early Childhood Education]]. He is the founder and coordenator of Brincadeira de Angola Project, which has the purpose of the playful teaching of capoeira applied to early childhood education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cepe.usp.br/wp-content/uploads/Mestre-Ferradura.pdf|title=CEPE USP|date=|accessdate=|publisher=|last=|first=}}</ref> The Brazilian Institute of Capoeira Education, project which he's president, he helps teachers to understand the concepts of Capoeira Education.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura|url=https://capoeiraibce.com/mestre-ferradura/|work=IBCE|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== Contributions to the Capoeira Education field ===\nMaster Ferradura possesses broad projection while difunding the Brincadeira de Angola method, which is a pedagic-philosophic based on the educational potential, applying Capoeira as a [[Pedagogy of the Oppressed|transformative pedagogic]] practice in autonomous subjects formation, and deconstruction of racism through the valorization of the african roots.<ref>{{cite web|title=Capoeira na escola \u00e9 uma janela para a desconstru\u00e7\u00e3o do racismo|url=https://ceert.org.br/noticias/educacao/25233/capoeira-na-escola-e-uma-janela-para-a-desconstrucao-do-racismo|work=CEERT|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura&#8217;s Great Insight on the Importance of Capoeira&#8217;s African Roots|url=https://www.capoeiranewsonline.com/mestre-ferraduras-great-insight-on-the-importance-of-capoeiras-african-roots/|work=www.capoeiranewsonline.com|date=2016-09-07|accessdate=2020-02-28|first=Rolha|last=Capoeira}}</ref> The basis of the methology is the ancestral knowledge of Capoeira, passed on from master to disciple in a traditional way. By balancing these popular and academic knowledge, the Brincadeira de Angola method suggest a Capoeira Pedagogy.<ref>{{cite web|title=17 de julho de 2019 - I\u00ea Camar\u00e1|url=https://tribunadoceara.com.br/blogs/ie-camara/2019/07/17/|work=tribunadoceara.com.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref> Another contribution by Mestre Ferradura to the Capoeira community was the production of \"''Movimento Novo''\" (New Movement), along with Mestre Itapu\u00e3 Beira-Mar, which brought discussions around the resulting violence  from the contact of capoeirists from different schools and proposes a pacific interaction to the new generations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Capoeira: O \u00daltimo Movimento Novo (Com V\u00eddeos)|url=https://capoeirariodejaneiro.com.br/geral/movimento-novo/|work=Capoeira - Rio|date=2019-01-03|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Capoeira |first1=Nestor |title=Capoeira: pequeno manual do jogador |date=1998 |publisher=Editora Record |isbn=978-85-01-04879-0 |url= |language=pt}}</ref>\n\n== Research and academic production ==\nIn the past decade, Mestre Ferradura has acted in the formation of teacher and promoting his pedagogic methodology in Brazil and Europe. His influences include [[Paulo Freire]], Muniz Sodr\u00e9, [[Marshall Rosenberg|Marshall Rosemberg]], Emilia Viotti da Costa, Elisa Larkin Nascimento, [[Thomas Skidmore|Thomas E. Skidmore]], Nestor Capoeira, [[Michel Foucault|Michel Foucalt]], [[A. S. Neill|A.S. Neil]], Terry Orlick, and [[Peter Slade]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - Biblioteca - Educa\u00e7\u00e3o F\u00edsica e jogos|url=http://www.educacaopublica.rj.gov.br/biblioteca/educacao_fisica/0009.html|work=www.educacaopublica.rj.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref> In his academic outreach, Mestre Ferradura travels and joins a number of formation programs and training of teachers and ''mestres'' in Brazilian and international Universities. Among the institutions which his courses and symposia have been ministrated, are included [[Federal Rural University of Rio de Janeiro|UFRR]], [[Federal University of Bahia|UFBA]], [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]], and ''Museu da Rep\u00fablica''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/rr/noticia/2013/11/mestres-dunga-e-ferradura-fazem-oficinas-de-capoeira-na-ufrr.html|title=Mestres Dunga e Ferradura fazem oficinas de capoeira na UFRR|date=|accessdate=|publisher=Globoesporte.com|last=|first=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=O ensino e a difus\u00e3o da capoeira foi debatido no XV Enecult \u2013 ENECULT|url=http://www.cult.ufba.br/enecult/o-ensino-e-a-difusao-da-capoeira-foi-debatido-no-xv-enecult/|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=CEPEUSP - Centro de Pr\u00e1ticas Esportivas da USP \u2013 Simp\u00f3sio Internacional de Capoeira|url=http://www.cepe.usp.br/?news=simposio-internacional-de-capoeira|work=www.cepe.usp.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mestre Ferradura|url=http://museus.cultura.gov.br/evento/5370/|work=Mapas Culturais|date=2019-05-08|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-BR|first=Mapas|last=Culturais}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Projeto Capoeirando ter\u00e1 aulas gratuitas para o p\u00fablico infantil|url=https://www.correiodoestado.com.br/arte-e-cultura/projeto-capoeirando-encerra-ciclo-de-formacao-para-professores-com/356973/|work=Correio do Estado|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Goi\u00e2nia recebe curso de Forma\u00e7\u00e3o Continuada em Capoeira na Educa\u00e7\u00e3o Infantil {{!}} Revista Zelo|url=http://revistazelo.com.br/post/goiania-recebe-curso-de-formacao-continuada-em-capoeira-na-educacao-infantil|work=revistazelo.com.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nHis most notable articles are:\n\n* ''Capoeira as a transformative educational practive''  (2010)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* ''Capoeira as pedagogic practice in early childhood education''  (2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=Revista Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - A Capoeira como pr\u00e1tica pedag\u00f3gica na Educa\u00e7\u00e3o Infantil|url=https://educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br/artigos/15/12/a-capoeira-como-prtica-pedaggica-na-educao-infantil|work=educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* ''Capoeira as a libertarian education for the formation of autonomous subjects - the teaching practices in Rio de Janeiro's Rodas de Rua'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|title=Revista Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica - Capoeira e educa\u00e7\u00e3o libert\u00e1ria para forma\u00e7\u00e3o de sujeitos aut\u00f4nomos \u2013 as pr\u00e1ticas de ensino nas rodas de rua do Rio de Janeiro|url=https://educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br/artigos/19/28/capoeira-e-educacao-libertaria-para-formacao-de-sujeitos-autonomos-r-as-praticas-de-ensino-nas-rodas-de-rua-do-rio-de-janeiro|work=educacaopublica.cecierj.edu.br|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* ''Brazilian racial ideology: the subjacent racism in comics magazines'' (2015)<ref>{{cite journal|last=Campos|first=Abigail Ferreira|date=2019-10-17|title=O CONCEITO DE IDEOLOGIA NAS HIST\u00d3RIAS EM QUADRINHOS|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.22533/at.ed.18519171026|publisher=Atena Editora|pages=283\u2013290|isbn=978-85-7247-718-5}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Capoeira de Rua.jpg|alt=Mestre Ferradura|thumb|Mestre Ferradura conducting a circle of Capoeira de Rua.|left]]\nHis works are academic references in authors of varied fields of pedagogy and studies in the african matrix, influencing and being cited in a series of monographies in Brasil.<ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Concep\u00e7\u00f5es de origem do ser humano e os conhecimentos das religi\u00f5es de matriz africana|url=http://repositorio.im.ufrrj.br:8080/jspui/bitstream/1235813/2932/1/Bruno%20Batista%20Cassiano%20-%20Jun%202016.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio UFRRJ|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=A capoeira como ferramenta metodol\u00f3gica na educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil: um relato de pr\u00e1ticas educativas|url=https://monografias.ufrn.br/jspui/bitstream/123456789/7147/10/CapoeiraFerramentaMetodo_Monografia_2018.pdf|journal=Monografias UFRN|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Uma interven\u00e7\u00e3o psicopedag\u00f3gica para educadores sociais de capoeira|url=https://www.editorarealize.com.br/revistas/conedu/trabalhos/TRABALHO_EV073_MD1_SA1_ID1065_21082017143144.pdf|journal=IV Congresso Nacional de Educa\u00e7\u00e3o - CONEDU|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=CONTRIBUI\u00c7\u00c3O DA CAPOEIRA NO PROGRAMA MAIS EDUCA\u00c7\u00c3O PARA A PROMO\u00c7\u00c3O DA CULTURA AFRO-BRASILEIRA: a experi\u00eancia de um Centro Integrado de Educa\u00e7\u00e3o P\u00fablica em Santa B\u00e1rbara d\u2019Oeste/SP|url=https://unisal.br/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Disserta%C3%A7%C3%A3o_Elisangela-L.-F.-de-Moraes.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio de Monografias da UNISAL|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=O conv\u00edvio da diferen\u00e7a: pr\u00e1ticas biopol\u00edticas no jogo de dentro e no jogo de fora|url=https://tede2.pucsp.br/bitstream/handle/21858/2/Livia%20Sernache%20Rios.pdf|journal=Resposit\u00f3rio de Disserta\u00e7\u00f5es PUC-SP|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=CAPOEIRA ANGOLA NA ESCOLA MUNICIPAL NOVA MORADA: perspectivas e pr\u00e1ticas educativas na constru\u00e7\u00e3o das identidades culturais|url=http://ww2.ppgeci.ufrpe.br/sites/ww2.ppgeci.ufrpe.br/files/documentos/dissertacao_ppgeci_n._30_danilo_santos_do_vale.pdf|journal=Reposit\u00f3rio do Programa de P\u00f3s-Gradua\u00e7\u00e3o da UFPE|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n== Social action ==\n\n\nMestre Ferradura's participations in social action includes occasional participation in activities of the Third Sector to regular governamental projects, such as:{{Quote box|quote=When we bring Capoeira de Rua for them, is a bit of culture and visibility. At the same time, we bring the idea of social circle, the look eye-in-the-eye, the care, the shelter, the belonging, and the knowledge that in that circle, you are just one capoeirist.|source=\u2014Mestre Ferradura, in an interview to Brazilian news program \"Balan\u00e7o Geral\", in December, 2019. [27]|align=right|width=33%}}{{Quote box|quote=Homeless people goes through a process of invisibilization. At Capeoira, we have necessarily to look at each other, interact, touch, know a bit of our feelings and needs of each other. The student's self-esteem is enhanced when he's seen, when he's heard, in his most basic needs of care, shelter, and belonging.|source=\u2014Mestre Ferradura, in interview to [[Rede Globo]], in August, 2019. [28]|align=right|width=33%}}\n\n* At the Benjamin Constant Institute, with a project of educating Capoeira to blind children<ref>{{cite web|title=Alunos fazem exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de capoeira aos pais|url=http://www.ibc.gov.br/component/content/article?id=865|work=www.ibc.gov.br|accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n* At [[:pt:Departamento_Geral_de_A\u00e7\u00f5es_S\u00f3cio_Educativas|DEGASE]], with institutionalized teenagers serving socio-educational measures<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bueno|first=Luzia|date=2005-12-15|title=G\u00eaneros da M\u00eddia Impressa no Material Did\u00e1tico e a Not\u00edcia Adaptada|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.5433/2237-4876.2005v8n2p9|journal=Signum: Estudos da Linguagem|volume=8|number=2|pages=9|doi=10.5433/2237-4876.2005v8n2p9|issn=2237-4876|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Carioca nota 10: Mestre Ferradura|url=https://vejario.abril.com.br/cidade/capoeirista-aulas-populacao-situacao-rua/|language=pt-BR}}</ref>\n* The Capoeira de Rua, with homeless people<ref>{{cite journal|date=2019-12-11|title=Vidas Invis\u00edveis: s\u00e9rie mostra um novo perfil dos moradores de rua|url=https://noticias.r7.com/rio-de-janeiro/balanco-geral-rj/videos/vidas-invisiveis-serie-mostra-um-novo-perfil-dos-moradores-de-rua-11122019|journal=R7.com|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Como Ser\u00e1? {{!}} Rede de solidariedade ajuda pessoas em situa\u00e7\u00e3o de rua no Rio de Janeiro {{!}} Globoplay|url=https://globoplay.globo.com/v/7863697/|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n* The Brazilian Capoeira-Education Institute for the Peace, in partnership with Gingando Pela Paz, [[UNESCO]], and [[:pt:Viva_Rio|Viva Rio]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Gingando pela Paz Haiti completa quatro anos|url=http://vivario.org.br/gingando-pela-paz-haiti-completa-quatro-anos/|work=Viva Rio|date=2012-10-01|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br}}</ref>\n\n== Artistic contributions ==\nIn the artistic fields, Mestre Ferradura has worked in a variety of direction of Capoeira, like:\n\n* ''Intr\u00e9pida Trupe'', in the Kronos show, having participated in the front commission of [[Mocidade Independente de Padre Miguel]], which won the ''Tamborim de Ouro'' Award in 1999.\n* With Paola Barreto Leblanc, when signed the direction of Capoeira and writing the script of the \"Mar\u00e9 Capoeira\" movie.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mar\u00e9 Capoeira|url=http://portacurtas.org.br/filme/?name=mare_capoeira|work=Porta Curtas|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=pt-br|last=PortaCurtas}}</ref>\n* With Jo\u00e3o Falc\u00e3o, director of \"[[\u00d3pera do Malandro]]\", when he did body conditioning of the troup at [[Theatro Municipal (Rio de Janeiro)|Theatro Municipal do Rio de Janeiro]].\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [http://www.capoeira.gov.br/user/infor/2200 Portal da Capoeira]\n* [https://capoeiraibce.com/ Instituto Brasileiro de Capoeira-Educa\u00e7\u00e3o]\n* [http://www.brincadeiradeangola.com.br/ Projeto Brincadeira de Angola]\n* [https://capoeirariodejaneiro.com.br/ Capoeira Rio de Janeiro]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Reflist}}<br />\n[[Category:Capoeira mestres]]\n[[Category:Brazilian capoeira practitioners]]\n[[Category:Pedagogy]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reference list duplication", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mestre_Ferradura"}
{"title_page": "Sir Samuel Garrard, 4th Baronet", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n{{Redirect|Samuel Garrard|Sir Samuel Garrard, 5th Baronet|Garrard baronets}}\n[[File:Sir Samuel Garrard, 4th Baronet.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Garrard by [[James Thornhill]], [[Guildhall Art Gallery]] London]]\n'''Sir Samuel Garrard, fourth Baronet''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|DL}} (1650\u20131724) of Lamer, Hertfordshire, was an English merchant and Tory politician who sat in the [[English House of Commons|English]] and  [[British House of Commons]] between 1701 and 1710. He was a city Alderman and was [[Lord Mayor of London]] from 1709 to 1710.\n\n== Early life ==\nGarrard was  born in 1650, the second son of Sir John Garrard, 2nd baronet, and his wife Jane Lambard, daughter of Sir Moulton Lambard of Westcombe. He  was a grandson of  the first baronet [[Sir John Garrard, 1st Baronet|Sir John Garrard]],  and maternal grandson of Dr. [[John Cosin]], [[Bishop of Durham]].<ref name=Cokayne1>{{Citation |editor-last=Cokayne |editor-first=George Edward |year=1900 |title= Complete Baronetage volume 1 (1611\u20131625) |url= https://archive.org/stream/cu31924092524374#page/n211/mode/2up | volume=1|  location=Exeter |publisher=William Pollard and Co| pages=| accessdate = 9 October 2018 }}</ref> His family  were connected with the city of London for more than two centuries and intermarriages took place between the Garrards and the city families of Roe, Gresham, and Barkham. Two of his ancestors were Lord Mayors, [[Sir William Garrard]] in 1555, and Sir John Garrard in 1601.  \n\nGarrard carried on business as a merchant first in Watling Street and afterwards in Warwick Court, Newgate Street. He married Elizabeth Poyner, daughter of George Poyner of  Codicote Bury, Hertfordshire on 16 October 1675. After she died without issue, he married as his second wife  Jane Bennett, daughter of Thomas Bennett of Salthrop, Wiltshire  on 22 January 1689. By the death, on 13 January 1700, of his brother [[Sir John Garrard, 3rd Baronet|Sir John Garrard]], the third baronet, he succeeded to the [[Garrard baronets|baronetcy]] and the family estate of Lamer in Wheathamstead, Hertfordshire.<ref name=Cokayne1/> He continued to reside and carry on business in London.\n\n== Career ==\nGarrard was elected alderman of the ward of Aldersgate on 3 March 1701.  In 1701, after a contested election, he was appointed [[Sheriff of London and Middlesex]].<ref name=ALD1>{{cite web |url = http://www.british-history.ac.uk/no-series/london-aldermen/hen3-1912/pp119-140  |title= , 'Chronological list of aldermen: 1701-1800', in The Aldermen of the City of London Temp. Henry III - 1912 (London, 1908), pp. 119-140 | author= Alfred P Beaven |publisher= British History Online| accessdate = 6 July 2019 }}</ref>  Garrard was returned as Tory [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Amersham (UK Parliament constituency)|Amersham]]  on the Drake interest at a by-election on 10 March 1701. He was blacklisted for opposing preparations for war with France. He was not returned again for Amersham until a by-election on 14 November 1702. He voted for the Tack on 28 November 1704. He was returned in a contest at Amersham at the [[1705 English general election]] and  voted against the Court candidate for Speaker on 25 October 1705. At the [[1708 British general election]], he was returned unopposed as Tory MP for Amersham.<ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url =http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1690-1715/member/garrard-sir-samuel-1651-1725 | title= GARRARD, Sir Samuel, 4th Bt. (1651-1725), of Lamer, Herts. and St. John the Evangelist, London| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 18 March 2019}}</ref> He served the office of Lord Mayor in 1709\u201310. There was no pageant at his inauguration, the practice having been finally dropped after the mayoralty of his predecessor, [[Sir Charles Duncombe]], for whom a pageant was prepared, but not exhibited on account of the death of [[Prince George of Denmark]]. At the beginning of his mayoralty, on 5 November 1709, Dr. [[Henry Sacheverell]] preached before him at St. Paul's his celebrated sermon advocating the doctrines of non-resistance and passive obedience, for which, and for an earlier sermon preached at Derby in August, he was impeached before the House of Lords. Garrard  is said to have approved of the sermon and to have sanctioned its publication, but this he repudiated in the House of Commons when Sacheverell pleaded the encouragement of the Lord Mayor in mitigation of his offence. During the serious riots which followed this trial Garrard exerted himself with much energy to restore order, and issued a proclamation, dated 30 March, prohibiting assemblies in the streets, the lighting of bonfires, and the sale of seditious books and pamphlets.\n\nIn October 1710 Garrard was chosen colonel of one of the regiments of the trained bands, and in the same year he became master of the [[Grocers' Company]], of which he was a liveryman.<ref name=ALD1/> However he did not stand for Parliament again at the [[1710 British general election]], probably as a result of his behavior during the Sacheverell affair.<ref name=HOP/> In October 1720, he was chosen as president of [[Bridewell and  Bethlehem Hospitals]],<ref name=ALD1/> and his portrait in full length, by an unknown artist, is preserved in the hall of Bridewell. Garrard  removed as Alderman to Bridge Ward Without in 1722, becoming senior alderman.<ref name=ALD1/> He was also deputy-lieutenant of Hertfordshire. \n\n==Death and legacy==\nGarrard died on 10 March 1724, and was buried in [[St Helen's Church, Wheathampstead|Wheathamstead Church]], where a monument remains to his memory. By his second wife, Jane, he had five daughters and three surviving sons, [[Sir Samuel Garrard, 5th Baronet|Samuel]] (died 1761), who succeeded to the baronetcy; Thomas (died 1758), who became [[Common Serjeant of London]]; and [[Sir Benet Garrard, 6th Baronet|Bennet]] (died 1767), who was Member of Parliament for Amersham and sixth and last baronet. His will, dated 20 December 1723, was proved in the P. C. C. on 1 April 1725. His property included estates in [[Exhall]] and [[Bedworth]], [[Warwickshire]]; in Wheathamstead, Hertfordshire; and in the city of London; besides stock and annuities in the [[South Sea Company]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{cite DNB|wstitle=Garrard, Samuel}}\n\n;Attribution\n{{DNB|wstitle=Garrard, Samuel}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Amersham (UK Parliament constituency)|Amersham]]\n| with=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n| years=1701\u20131701\n| before=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] | before2=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n| after=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] | after2=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=Member of Parliament for Amersham\n| with= [[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]] 1702\u20131705, 1707\n| with2=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] 1705\u20131707\n| years=1702\u20131707\n| before=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]]| before2=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n| after=Parliament of Great Britain\n}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Amersham (UK Parliament constituency)|Amersham]]\n| with=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]] 1707\u20131708\n| with2=[[Francis Duncombe (MP)|Francis Duncombe]] 1708\u20131710\n| years=1707\u20131710\n| before=Parliament of England\n| after=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]] | after2=[[Francis Duncombe (MP)|Francis Duncombe]]\n}}\n{{s-civ}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[File:Coat of Arms of The City of London.svg|55px|center]] [[List of Lord Mayors of London|Lord Mayor of London]]\n|years= 1709&ndash;1710\n| before=  [[Charles Duncombe (Lord Mayor of the City of London)|Sir Charles Duncombe]] \n| after=  [[Sir Gilbert Heathcote, 1st Baronet]] }}\n\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Garrard baronets|Baronet Garrard]]\n| before=[[Sir John Garrard, 3rd Baronet|Sir John Garrard]]\n| after=[[Sir Samuel Garrard, 5th Baronet|Sir Samuel Garrard]]\n| years=1700\u20131724\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garrard, Samuel}}\n[[Category:1650 births]]\n[[Category:1724 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sheriffs of the City of London]]\n[[Category:18th-century lord mayors of London]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1701]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1701\u20131702]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1702\u20131705]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1705\u20131707]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1707\u20131708]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1708\u20131710]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Baronets in the Baronetage of England]]\n[[Category:Deputy Lieutenants of Hertfordshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n{{Redirect|Samuel Garrard|Sir Samuel Garrard, 5th Baronet|Garrard baronets}}\n[[File:Sir Samuel Garrard, 4th Baronet.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Garrard by [[James Thornhill]], [[Guildhall Art Gallery]] London]]\n'''Sir Samuel Garrard, fourth Baronet''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|DL}} (1650\u20131724) of Lamer, Hertfordshire, was an English merchant and Tory politician who sat in the [[English House of Commons|English]] and  [[British House of Commons]] between 1701 and 1710. He was a city Alderman and was [[Lord Mayor of London]] from 1709 to 1710.\n\n== Early life ==\nGarrard was  born in 1650, the second son of Sir John Garrard, 2nd baronet, and his wife Jane Lambard, daughter of Sir Moulton Lambard of Westcombe. He  was a grandson of  the first baronet [[Sir John Garrard, 1st Baronet|Sir John Garrard]],  and maternal grandson of Dr. [[John Cosin]], [[Bishop of Durham]].<ref name=Cokayne1>{{Citation |editor-last=Cokayne |editor-first=George Edward |year=1900 |title= Complete Baronetage volume 1 (1611\u20131625) |url= https://archive.org/stream/cu31924092524374#page/n211/mode/2up | volume=1|  location=Exeter |publisher=William Pollard and Co| pages=| accessdate = 9 October 2018 }}</ref> His family  were connected with the city of London for more than two centuries and intermarriages took place between the Garrards and the city families of Roe, Gresham, and Barkham. Two of his ancestors were Lord Mayors, [[Sir William Garrard]] in 1555, and Sir John Garrard in 1601.  \n\nGarrard carried on business as a merchant first in Watling Street and afterwards in Warwick Court, Newgate Street. He married Elizabeth Poyner, daughter of George Poyner of  Codicote Bury, Hertfordshire on 16 October 1675. After she died without issue, he married as his second wife  Jane Bennett, daughter of Thomas Bennett of Salthrop, Wiltshire  on 22 January 1689. By the death, on 13 January 1700, of his brother [[Sir John Garrard, 3rd Baronet|Sir John Garrard]], the third baronet, he succeeded to the [[Garrard baronets|baronetcy]] and the family estate of Lamer in Wheathamstead, Hertfordshire.<ref name=Cokayne1/> He continued to reside and carry on business in London.\n\n== Career ==\nGarrard was elected alderman of the ward of Aldersgate on 3 March 1701.  In 1701, after a contested election, he was appointed [[Sheriff of London and Middlesex]].<ref name=ALD1>{{cite web |url = http://www.british-history.ac.uk/no-series/london-aldermen/hen3-1912/pp119-140  |title= , 'Chronological list of aldermen: 1701-1800', in The Aldermen of the City of London Temp. Henry III - 1912 (London, 1908), pp. 119-140 | author= Alfred P Beaven |publisher= British History Online| accessdate = 6 July 2019 }}</ref>  Garrard was returned as Tory [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Amersham (UK Parliament constituency)|Amersham]]  on the Drake interest at a by-election on 10 March 1701. He was blacklisted for opposing preparations for war with France. He was not returned again for Amersham until a by-election on 14 November 1702. He voted for the Tack on 28 November 1704. He was returned in a contest at Amersham at the [[1705 English general election]] and  voted against the Court candidate for Speaker on 25 October 1705. At the [[1708 British general election]], he was returned unopposed as Tory MP for Amersham.<ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url =http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1690-1715/member/garrard-sir-samuel-1651-1725 | title= GARRARD, Sir Samuel, 4th Bt. (1651-1725), of Lamer, Herts. and St. John the Evangelist, London| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 18 March 2019}}</ref> He served the office of Lord Mayor in 1709-10. There was no pageant at his inauguration, the practice having been finally dropped after the mayoralty of his predecessor, [[Sir Charles Duncombe]], for whom a pageant was prepared, but not exhibited on account of the death of [[Prince George of Denmark]]. At the beginning of his mayoralty, on 5 November 1709, Dr. [[Henry Sacheverell]] preached before him at St. Paul's his celebrated sermon advocating the doctrines of non-resistance and passive obedience, for which, and for an earlier sermon preached at Derby in August, he was impeached before the House of Lords. Garrard  is said to have approved of the sermon and to have sanctioned its publication, but this he repudiated in the House of Commons when Sacheverell pleaded the encouragement of the Lord Mayor in mitigation of his offence. During the serious riots which followed this trial Garrard exerted himself with much energy to restore order, and issued a proclamation, dated 30 March, prohibiting assemblies in the streets, the lighting of bonfires, and the sale of seditious books and pamphlets.\n\nIn October 1710 Garrard was chosen colonel of one of the regiments of the trained bands, and in the same year he became master of the [[Grocers' Company]], of which he was a liveryman.<ref name=ALD1/> However he did not stand for Parliament again at the [[1710 British general election]], probably as a result of his behavior during the Sacheverell affair.<ref name=HOP/> In October 1720, he was chosen as president of [[Bridewell and  Bethlehem Hospitals]],<ref name=ALD1/> and his portrait in full length, by an unknown artist, is preserved in the hall of Bridewell. Garrard  removed as Alderman to Bridge Ward Without in 1722, becoming senior alderman.<ref name=ALD1/> He was also deputy-lieutenant of Hertfordshire. \n\n==Death and legacy==\nGarrard died on 10 March 1724, and was buried in [[St Helen's Church, Wheathampstead|Wheathamstead Church]], where a monument remains to his memory. By his second wife, Jane, he had five daughters and three surviving sons, [[Sir Samuel Garrard, 5th Baronet|Samuel]] (died 1761), who succeeded to the baronetcy; Thomas (died 1758), who became [[Common Serjeant of London]]; and [[Sir Benet Garrard, 6th Baronet|Bennet]] (died 1767), who was Member of Parliament for Amersham and sixth and last baronet. His will, dated 20 December 1723, was proved in the P. C. C. on 1 April 1725. His property included estates in [[Exhall]] and [[Bedworth]], [[Warwickshire]]; in Wheathamstead, Hertfordshire; and in the city of London; besides stock and annuities in the [[South Sea Company]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{cite DNB|wstitle=Garrard, Samuel}}\n\n;Attribution\n{{DNB|wstitle=Garrard, Samuel}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Amersham (UK Parliament constituency)|Amersham]]\n| with=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n| years=1701\u20131701\n| before=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] | before2=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n| after=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] | after2=[[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=Member of Parliament for Amersham\n| with= [[John Drake (MP)|John Drake]] 1702\u20131705, 1707\n| with2=[[William Cheyne, 2nd Viscount Newhaven|Viscount Newhaven]] 1705\u20131707\n| years=1702